      "content": "I hear how desperate it feels when every tool seems to lead back to the same place, and I want to reassure you that this relentless pattern isn't a personal failure but a common neurological response known as relapse. The feeling that there is only one exit—\"stopping everything\"—is a result of the loop convincing you that change is impossible, rather than a reflection of reality. Because relapse is often driven by environmental triggers and organizational structures, pulling back completely prevents learning the critical steps that eventually lead to lasting freedom from the cycle.",
